Your file has two major mistakes that are causing all the errors:

1. You placed useState OUTSIDE the component

This is illegal in React.

You wrote this outside:

js
const [customerEmail, setCustomerEmail] = useState("");

Hooks must always be inside a component.

2. You used CustomerEmail (capital C)

React is case-sensitive customerEmail and CustomerEmail are NOT the same.

3. You used gst but that variable does NOT exist

You named it gstAmount, not gst.

4. You used <SendOrderEmail> without importing it

**I fixed everything and rewrote your Cart.jsx completely.

Copypaste this full corrected version:**

Corrected Cart.jsx

jsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { useSelector, useDispatch } from "react-redux";
import { removeFromCart, incrementItem, decrementItem, applyCoupon } from "./Store";
import SendOrderEmail from "./SendOrderEmail"; // <-- Make sure this file exists

function Cart() {
  const dispatch = useDispatch();

  const cartitems = useSelector((state) => state.cart);
  const coupon = useSelector((state) => state.coupon);

  // FIXED: email state must be inside the component
  const [customerEmail, setCustomerEmail] = useState("");

  const [manualDiscount, setManualDiscount] = useState(0);
  const [couponInput, setCouponInput] = useState("");

  // ---- TOTAL ----
  const totalAmount = cartitems.reduce(
    (total, item) => total + item.price * item.quantity,
    0
  );

  // ---- FINAL DISCOUNT LOGIC ----
  const finalDiscountPercent = coupon.applied ? coupon.discount : manualDiscount;

  // ---- CALCULATIONS ----
  let discountAmount = (totalAmount * finalDiscountPercent) / 100;
  let priceAfterDiscount = totalAmount - discountAmount;
  let gstAmount = (priceAfterDiscount * 18) / 100;
  let netAmount = priceAfterDiscount + gstAmount;

  return (
    <>
      <h1>Welcome Cart....</h1>

      {cartitems.length === 0 ? (
        <h2>Your cart is empty</h2>
      ) : (
        <>
          <ul>
            {cartitems.map((item) => (
              <li key={item.id}>
                {item.name} - {item.price}  {item.quantity}
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(removeFromCart(item.id))}>
                  Remove
                </button>
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(incrementItem(item.id))}>+</button>
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(decrementItem(item.id))}>-</button>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>

          {/* DISCOUNT */}
          <h2>Choose Discount</h2>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(10)}>10%</button>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(20)}>20%</button>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(30)}>30%</button>

          <h3>Selected Discount: {manualDiscount}%</h3>

          {/* COUPON */}
          <h2>Apply Coupon</h2>
          <input
            type="text"
            placeholder="Enter coupon"
            value={couponInput}
            onChange={(e) => setCouponInput(e.target.value)}
          />

          <button onClick={() => dispatch(applyCoupon(couponInput))}>
            Apply Coupon
          </button>

          <p>{coupon.message}</p>

          {/* BILLING */}
          <h2>Billing Details</h2>
          <h3>Total Amount: {totalAmount}</h3>
          <h3>Discount ({finalDiscountPercent}%): {discountAmount}</h3>
          <h3>Amount After Discount: {priceAfterDiscount}</h3>
          <h3>GST (18%): {gstAmount}</h3>
          <h2>Net Amount to Pay: {netAmount}</h2>

          {/* EMAIL SECTION */}
          <div className="email-section">
            <h4>Enter your email to receive order details:</h4>

            <input
              type="email"
              placeholder="Enter your email"
              value={customerEmail}
              onChange={(e) => setCustomerEmail(e.target.value)}
            />

            <SendOrderEmail
              cartItems={cartitems}
              netAmount={netAmount}
              tax={gstAmount}
              totalAmount={totalAmount}
              customerEmail={customerEmail}
            />
          </div>
        </>
      )}
    </>
  );
}

export default Cart;

Great your Cart component is correct, but now you need the SendOrderEmail.js file to actually send the email.

Below is a working SendOrderEmail.js, using EmailJS (the easiest method no backend required).

Step 1: Install EmailJS library

Run this in your project:

nginx
npm install emailjs-com

Step 2: Create EmailJS account

Go to: https://www.emailjs.com
Then:

  1. Create an account

  2. Create Email Service you get: SERVICE_ID

  3. Create Email Template you get: TEMPLATE_ID

  4. Go to Account API Keys get PUBLIC_KEY

Step 3: Create SendOrderEmail.js

Create a file: SendOrderEmail.js inside your src folder.

Paste this code:

jsx
import React from "react";
import emailjs from "emailjs-com";

function SendOrderEmail({ cartItems, netAmount, tax, totalAmount, customerEmail }) {

  const sendEmail = () => {
    if (!customerEmail) {
      alert("Please enter your email");
      return;
    }

    const orderList = cartItems
      .map(item => `${item.name} (x${item.quantity}) = ${item.price * item.quantity}`)
      .join("\n");

    const templateParams = {
      to_email: customerEmail,
      order_items: orderList,
      total_amount: totalAmount,
      tax_amount: tax,
      net_amount: netAmount,
    };

    emailjs
      .send(
        "YOUR_SERVICE_ID",    // Replace
        "YOUR_TEMPLATE_ID",   // Replace
        templateParams,
        "YOUR_PUBLIC_KEY"     // Replace
      )
      .then(
        (response) => {
          alert("Order email sent successfully!");
        },
        (error) => {
          console.error("Email error:", error);
          alert("Failed to send email");
        }
      );
  };

  return (
    <button onClick={sendEmail}>
      Send Order Email
    </button>
  );
}

export default SendOrderEmail;

jsx
import React from 'react';
import emailjs from 'emailjs-com';

function SendOrderEmail({ cartItems, netAmount, tax, totalAmount, customerEmail }) {
  const sendEmail = () => {
    if (!customerEmail) {
      alert("Please enter your email");
      return;
    }

    let templateparams = {
      orders: cartItems.map(item => ({
        name: item.name,
        units: item.quantity,
        price: item.price
      })),
      order_id: Date.now(),
      totalAmount: totalAmount.toFixed(2),
      tax: tax.toFixed(2),
      email: customerEmail
    };

    emailjs.send(
      "service_cicidrob",
      "template_sdzzkks",
      templateparams,
      "KWKJMPkVuzo7k_-GU"
    )
    .then((response) => {
      alert("Email sent successfully");
    })
    .catch((error) => {
      console.error("Email sending error:", error);
      alert("Failed to send email. Please try again.");
    });
  };

  return (
    <>
      <button onClick={sendEmail}>Send Order Email</button>
    </>
  );
}

export default SendOrderEmail;

Just in case you need a quick example of applyCoupon reducer:

js
const couponSlice = createSlice({
  name: 'coupon',
  initialState: {
    applied: false,
    discount: 0,
    message: '',
  },
  reducers: {
    applyCoupon: (state, action) => {
      const code = action.payload.trim().toUpperCase();

      const validCoupons = {
        FOOD10: 10,
        SAVE20: 20,
        SUPER30: 30,
      };

      if (validCoupons[code]) {
        state.applied = true;
        state.discount = validCoupons[code];
        state.message = `Coupon ${code} applied!`;
      } else {
        state.applied = false;
        state.discount = 0;
        state.message = 'Invalid coupon code';
      }
    },
  },
});

Cart.jsx

jsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { useSelector, useDispatch } from "react-redux";
import { removeFromCart, incrementItem, decrementItem, applyCoupon } from "./Store";
import SendOrderEmail from "./SendOrderEmail";

function Cart() {
  const dispatch = useDispatch();

  const cartitems = useSelector((state) => state.cart);
  const coupon = useSelector((state) => state.coupon);

  const [customerEmail, setCustomerEmail] = useState("");
  const [manualDiscount, setManualDiscount] = useState(0);
  const [couponInput, setCouponInput] = useState("");

  // Calculate total amount
  const totalAmount = cartitems.reduce(
    (total, item) => total + item.price * item.quantity,
    0
  );

  // Determine discount
  const finalDiscountPercent = coupon.applied ? coupon.discount : manualDiscount;

  // Calculate pricing breakdown
  const discountAmount = (totalAmount * finalDiscountPercent) / 100;
  const priceAfterDiscount = totalAmount - discountAmount;
  const gstAmount = (priceAfterDiscount * 18) / 100;
  const netAmount = priceAfterDiscount + gstAmount;

  console.log("Customer email:", customerEmail); // Debug log

  return (
    <>
      <h1>Welcome Cart....</h1>

      {cartitems.length === 0 ? (
        <h2>Your cart is empty</h2>
      ) : (
        <>
          <ul>
            {cartitems.map((item) => (
              <li key={item.id}>
                {item.name} - {item.price}  {item.quantity}
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(removeFromCart(item.id))}>
                  Remove
                </button>
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(incrementItem(item.id))}>+</button>
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(decrementItem(item.id))}>-</button>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>

          {/* Discount Selection */}
          <h2>Choose Discount</h2>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(10)}>10%</button>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(20)}>20%</button>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(30)}>30%</button>

          <h3>Selected Discount: {manualDiscount}%</h3>

          {/* Coupon Input */}
          <h2>Apply Coupon</h2>
          <input
            type="text"
            placeholder="Enter coupon"
            value={couponInput}
            onChange={(e) => setCouponInput(e.target.value)}
          />
          <button onClick={() => dispatch(applyCoupon(couponInput))}>Apply Coupon</button>

          <p>{coupon.message}</p>

          {/* Billing Details */}
          <h2>Billing Details</h2>
          <h3>Total Amount: {totalAmount.toFixed(2)}</h3>
          <h3>Discount ({finalDiscountPercent}%): {discountAmount.toFixed(2)}</h3>
          <h3>Amount After Discount: {priceAfterDiscount.toFixed(2)}</h3>
          <h3>GST (18%): {gstAmount.toFixed(2)}</h3>
          <h2>Net Amount to Pay: {netAmount.toFixed(2)}</h2>

          {/* Email Section */}
          <div className="email-section">
            <h4>Enter your email to receive order details:</h4>
            <input
              type="email"
              placeholder="Enter your email"
              value={customerEmail}
              onChange={(e) => setCustomerEmail(e.target.value)}
            />

            <SendOrderEmail
              cartItems={cartitems}
              netAmount={netAmount}
              tax={gstAmount}
              totalAmount={totalAmount}
              customerEmail={customerEmail}
            />
          </div>
        </>
      )}
    </>
  );
}

export default Cart;

// Cart.jsx
import React, { useState } from "react";
import { useSelector, useDispatch } from "react-redux";
import { removeFromCart, incrementItem, decrementItem, applyCoupon } from "./Store";
import SendOrderEmail from "./SendOrderEmail";

function Cart() {
  const dispatch = useDispatch();

  const cartitems = useSelector((state) => state.cart);
  const coupon = useSelector((state) => state.coupon);

  const [customerEmail, setCustomerEmail] = useState("");
  const [manualDiscount, setManualDiscount] = useState(0);
  const [couponInput, setCouponInput] = useState("");

  const totalAmount = cartitems.reduce((total, item) => total + item.price * item.quantity, 0);

  const finalDiscountPercent = coupon.applied ? coupon.discount : manualDiscount;

  const discountAmount = (totalAmount * finalDiscountPercent) / 100;
  const priceAfterDiscount = totalAmount - discountAmount;
  const gstAmount = (priceAfterDiscount * 18) / 100;
  const netAmount = priceAfterDiscount + gstAmount;

  return (
    <>
      <h1>Welcome Cart....</h1>

      {cartitems.length === 0 ? (
        <h2>Your cart is empty</h2>
      ) : (
        <>
          <ul>
            {cartitems.map((item) => (
              <li key={item.id}>
                {item.name} - {item.price}  {item.quantity}
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(removeFromCart(item.id))}>Remove</button>
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(incrementItem(item.id))}>+</button>
                <button onClick={() => dispatch(decrementItem(item.id))}>-</button>
              </li>
            ))}
          </ul>

          <h2>Choose Discount</h2>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(10)}>10%</button>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(20)}>20%</button>
          <button onClick={() => setManualDiscount(30)}>30%</button>

          <h3>Selected Discount: {manualDiscount}%</h3>

          <h2>Apply Coupon</h2>
          <input
            type="text"
            placeholder="Enter coupon"
            value={couponInput}
            onChange={(e) => setCouponInput(e.target.value)}
          />
          <button onClick={() => dispatch(applyCoupon(couponInput))}>Apply Coupon</button>
          <p>{coupon.message}</p>

          <h2>Billing Details</h2>
          <h3>Total Amount: {totalAmount.toFixed(2)}</h3>
          <h3>Discount ({finalDiscountPercent}%): {discountAmount.toFixed(2)}</h3>
          <h3>Amount After Discount: {priceAfterDiscount.toFixed(2)}</h3>
          <h3>GST (18%): {gstAmount.toFixed(2)}</h3>
          <h2>Net Amount to Pay: {netAmount.toFixed(2)}</h2>

          <div className="email-section">
            <h4>Enter your email to receive order details:</h4>
            <input
              type="email"
              placeholder="Enter your email"
              value={customerEmail}
              onChange={(e) => setCustomerEmail(e.target.value)}
            />
            <SendOrderEmail
              cartItems={cartitems}
              netAmount={netAmount}
              tax={gstAmount}
              totalAmount={totalAmount}
              customerEmail={customerEmail}
            />
          </div>
        </>
      )}
    </>
  );
}

export default Cart;

import React from "react";
import emailjs from "emailjs-com";

function SendOrderEmail({ cartItems, netAmount, tax, totalAmount, customerEmail }) {
  const sendEmail = () => {
    // Email validation (simple)
    if (!customerEmail || !/\S+@\S+\.\S+/.test(customerEmail)) {
      alert("Please enter a valid email before sending the order.");
      return;
    }

    // Prepare orders string
    const ordersString = cartItems
      .map(item => `${item.name} - Qty: ${item.quantity}, Price: ${item.price}`)
      .join("\n");

    // Template params matching EmailJS template variables
    const templateParams = {
      email: customerEmail,
      order_id: Date.now().toString(),
      orders: ordersString,
      totalAmount: totalAmount.toFixed(2),
      tax: tax.toFixed(2),
    };

    // Send email via EmailJS
    emailjs
      .send(
        "service_cicidrob",
        "template_sdzzkks",
        templateParams,
        "KWKJMPkVuzo7k_-GU"  // Use your correct public key here
      )
      .then(() => {
        alert("Email sent successfully!");
      })
      .catch(error => {
        alert("Failed to send email. See console for details.");
        console.error("EmailJS error:", error);
      });
  };

  return <button onClick={sendEmail}>Send Order Email</button>;
}

export default SendOrderEmail;

import React from "react";
import emailjs from "emailjs-com";

function SendOrderEmail({ cartItems, netAmount, tax, totalAmount, customerEmail }) {
  const sendEmail = () => {
    // Simple email validation
    if (!customerEmail || !/\S+@\S+\.\S+/.test(customerEmail)) {
      alert("Please enter a valid email before sending the order.");
      return;
    }

    // Prepare order details string
    const ordersString = cartItems
      .map(item => `${item.name} - Qty: ${item.quantity}, Price: ${item.price}`)
      .join("\n");

    // Template parameters matching your EmailJS template variables
    const templateParams = {
      email: customerEmail,
      order_id: Date.now().toString(),
      orders: ordersString,
      totalAmount: totalAmount.toFixed(2),
      tax: tax.toFixed(2),
    };

    // Send email using EmailJS service

        templateParams,
        "KWKJMPkVuzo7k_-GU"     // Your EmailJS Public Key

  };

}
